# CODEOWNERS for the Ghola monorepo.
#
# These rules force review approval for hardening-sensitive paths. The
# evidence-gate workflow (.github/workflows/evidence-gate.yml) re-derives
# every stream's commitment on PR — but baseline updates (the
# `evidence-baseline.json` file) can ONLY land with an explicit human
# approval from this set, so a code change that silently breaks an
# invariant cannot be papered over by regenerating the baseline.

# Repository default — protocol & infra owners
*                                          @anndrrson

# Hardening evidence (the gate's source of truth)
/.github/evidence-baseline.json            @anndrrson
/scripts/evidence/                         @anndrrson
/.github/workflows/evidence-gate.yml       @anndrrson
/.github/workflows/supply-chain.yml        @anndrrson
/.github/workflows/sbom.yml                @anndrrson
/.github/workflows/fuzz.yml                @anndrrson

# Shielded-pool program — Stream 4 surface (governance, custody, vk)
/programs/said-shielded-pool/              @anndrrson

# Cryptographic core — auditor-facing artifacts
/crates/said-shielded-pool-circuits/       @anndrrson
/crates/said-shielded-pool-invariants/     @anndrrson
/crates/said-shielded-pool-types/          @anndrrson
/docs/shielded-pool/SPEC.md                @anndrrson
/docs/shielded-pool/INVARIANTS.md          @anndrrson
/docs/shielded-pool/GOVERNANCE.md          @anndrrson
/docs/shielded-pool/UPGRADE_RUNBOOK.md     @anndrrson
/docs/shielded-pool/AUDIT_PACKAGE.md       @anndrrson

# Secret-handling surfaces
/crates/common-secrets/                    @anndrrson
/crates/common-log/                        @anndrrson

# Supply-chain policy
/deny.toml                                 @anndrrson
/.cargo/audit.toml                         @anndrrson

# Note: replace @anndrrson with the production multisig handle (e.g.
# @ghola/security-council) before tagging for external audit. The
# CODEOWNERS file itself should require ≥2 approvers in production.
